data.title: US military defied Trump ban, used Anthropic in Iran strike: WSJUS military used Anthropic's Claude AI for intel analysis in Iran strike despite Trump ban.
data.description: Reportedly, the US military utilized Anthropic's Claude AI for intelligence analysis and targeting during a strike on Iran shortly after President Trump issued a ban on the company's technology. The strike occurred within hours of the ban, showcasing the military's reliance on the AI despite the restrictions imposed by the government. This highlights the significance of Anthropic's technology in military operations, emphasizing its crucial role in decision-making processes. The incident underscores the complexities surrounding the use of AI in defense and national security strategies, indicating a shift towards advanced technological solutions in modern warfare.

data.title: Dr. Samir J. Serhan appointed CEO of Acwa by Board of Directors, previously President of Saudi Arabia and Middle East.
data.description: Today, Dr. Samir J. Serhan has been appointed as the new CEO by the Board of Directors at Acwa. Dr. Serhan, who was formerly the President of Acwa for Saudi Arabia and the Middle East, also served as the Chief Operating Officer at the US-based Air Products. Meanwhile, Marco Arcelli, who had been the CEO of Acwa since March 2023, will continue in the company as an advisor.
